<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT7"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART VII BAIL [rr 54&#x2013;60]">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT7" type="ext"/>PART VII</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">BAIL [rr 54&#x2013;60]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,685] r 54 Bail bonds">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54" type="ext"/>[255,685]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Bail bonds</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>54</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Bail on behalf of a party must be given by filing a bail bond.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The bail bond must be in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F20" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 20</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, and, unless the court or a Registrar otherwise orders, must be signed by 2 sureties.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 327 of 1993  r 6; SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The sureties must sign the bond before:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>a Registrar of any court that has jurisdiction under the Act in a proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>a person before whom affidavits for use in such a court may be sworn, other than:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.B.I"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.B.I" type="ext"/>(i)</lilabel>
<p><text>a person who is acting as an Australian legal practitioner for the party on whose behalf bail is to be given in the proceeding; or</text></p>
</li><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.B.II"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.3.B.II" type="ext"/>(ii)</lilabel>
<p><text>a person whose partner, employer or employee, is acting as an Australian legal practitioner for the party on whose behalf bail is to be given in the proceeding.</text></p>
</li></l></li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3)  subst SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.18, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A partnership or corporation carrying on business in the jurisdiction in which the proceeding is commenced may act as a surety.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (4)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.18, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R54.5" type="ext"/>(5)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If both sureties signing the bond under subrule (3) are corporations, the corporations must not be related bodies corporate within the meaning of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="006K" refpt="ACLL.CL.S9" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">section 9</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Corporations Act 2001.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (5)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.18, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,690] r 55 Notice of bail">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55" type="ext"/>[255,690]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Notice of bail</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>55</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A party on whose behalf bail is to be given must serve a notice of bail and a copy of the bond on each other party to the proceeding.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Notice of bail must be in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F21" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 21</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,695] r 56 Objection to bail">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56" type="ext"/>[255,695]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Objection to bail</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>56</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A party who has been served with a notice of bail may, within 24 hours after service of the notice, file a notice of objection in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F22" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 22</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 against the sufficiency of the proposed surety.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Registrar must, on a date and at a time and place appointed by the Registrar, determine whether the proposed surety is sufficient.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Not less than 24 hours before the time so appointed, notice of the hearing of the objection in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F23" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 23</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, must be served:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>on each other party to the proceeding; and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>personally upon the proposed surety.</text></p>
</li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3A"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3A" type="ext"/>(3A)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Before the date appointed by the Registrar under subrule (2), the proposed surety must file and serve on each other party to the proceeding an affidavit regarding its financial circumstances.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3A)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.19, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B" type="ext"/>(3B)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The affidavit must set out at least the following matters:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the proposed surety&#x2019;s current and non-current assets and liabilities (including contingent liabilities);</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>current proceedings in which the proposed surety is a party;</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>whether, in the 5 years before the date of the affidavit, the proposed surety has been the subject of any demand under a law relating to bankruptcy or insolvency;</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.D"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3B.D" type="ext"/>(d)</lilabel>
<p><text>whether, in the 5 years before the date of the affidavit, the proposed surety has been made bankrupt, placed in administration or receivership or has been the subject of bankruptcy or winding up proceedings or of a garnishee order.</text></p>
</li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3B)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.19, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3C"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3C" type="ext"/>(3C)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Registrar may direct the proposed surety to file and serve a supplementary affidavit setting out additional information regarding:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3C.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3C.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the proposed surety&#x2019;s financial circumstances; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3C.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3C.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>other circumstances relating to the proposed surety&#x2019;s sufficiency;</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<p><text>as the Registrar considers appropriate.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3C)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.19, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A proposed surety who has been served with a notice of the hearing of the objection under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.3" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subrule (3)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 must attend on the date and at the time and place so appointed, and from day to day thereafter at that time and place, unless excused by the Registrar.</text></p>
<p><text>Penalty:   10 penalty units.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (4)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.20 and 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A" type="ext"/>(4A)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Registrar may:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>adjourn from time to time the hearing appointed under subrule (2); and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>allow the proposed surety or a party to the proceeding to file and serve additional affidavit material regarding the sufficiency of the proposed surety; and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A.C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4A.C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>give directions regarding such matters as the Registrar considers appropriate.</text></p>
</li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (4A)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.21, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4B"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.4B" type="ext"/>(4B)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If a material adverse change occurs in relation to a matter or circumstance mentioned in an affidavit filed under this rule, the proposed surety must, within 7 days after that change occurs, file and serve on each other party to the proceeding another affidavit setting out the changed details in relation to the matter.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (4B)  insrt SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.21, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.5" type="ext"/>(5)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If the Registrar determines that the proposed surety is sufficient, then, unless the court otherwise orders, the costs of or incidental to the objection must be paid by the party objecting.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (15)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,700] r 57 Filing bonds">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57" type="ext"/>[255,700]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Filing bonds</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>57</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Subject to 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subrule (2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, a bail bond must not be filed before the end of 24 hours after notice of the bail has been served under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R55" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">rule 55</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R57.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If a party has objected to the sufficiency of a proposed surety, the bail bond must not be filed until the Registrar has determined that the proposed surety is sufficient.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R58"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,705] r 58 Sureties bound">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R58" type="ext"/>[255,705]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Sureties bound</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>58</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A surety is bound by a bail bond from the time when the bond is filed.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,710] r 59 Court may vary bail">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59" type="ext"/>[255,710]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Court may vary bail</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>59</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The court may, by order, reduce the amount of bail in respect of which a bail bond has been filed.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If the court makes an order under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subrule (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, it may also make such orders as are necessary to give effect to the order.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.38, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Subrules (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 and 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">(2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 do not affect any other power of the court.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R59.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255710-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,710.5]">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,710.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_ACT_1988-34" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Act 1988</remotelink> s 34(1).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255710-5" type="ext"/>[255,710.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>This rule spells out the power of the court, at general law, to reduce the amount of bail, either as part of an application for release or in a separate proceeding. This power does not extend to non-court sanctioned arrangements. Such arrangements are a matter for agreement between the parties except to the extent that excessive demands give rise to a right of damages under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADA88.S34.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 34(1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Admiralty Act 1988 (Cth).</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R60"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,715] r 60 Costs of bail">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R60" type="ext"/>[255,715]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Costs of bail</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>60</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Subject to 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R56.5" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subrule 56(5)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, the costs of and incidental to obtaining bail are taken to be costs in the proceeding.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[r 60  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R60.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255715-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,715.5]">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,715.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_REG_1988-269" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Rules 1988</remotelink> r 60.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_REG_1952-23" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">High Court Rules 1952</remotelink> O 11 r 20.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255715-5" type="ext"/>[255,715.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>A defendant may incur a commission or fee in arranging for sureties to provide bail. Under the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.ADR52" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Admiralty Rules 1952 (NSW)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, there was no express provision for the court to order an unsuccessful plaintiff to pay to the defendant the defendant's costs in obtaining bail. 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R60" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Rule 60</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 follows 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.HCR.O11.20" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">O 11 r 20</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the High Court Rules in treating bail costs as within the ambit of costs essential for the conduct of the action and therefore recoverable. It would still be open to the court in an appropriate case in its general discretion to refuse to order the unsuccessful plaintiff to pay the defendant's bail costs: see ALRC, Report No 33, <emph typestyle="it">Civil Admiralty Jurisdiction</emph>, 1986, para 301.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
